Description: Wooden naked female figure holding cat to chest; feet lost.
Curator's comments: Published: PM viii, p. 699. Egypt's Dazzling Sun, (Cleveland 1992), p.466, Tab. 3. Amenophis III, (Pais 1993), p.400, Tab. 3. G. Robins, Reflections of Women in the New Kingdom (1995), p. 120-1, pl.79. Malek, The Cat in Ancient Egypt, 1993, p.72. H.R. Hall, JEA XV, p.236.
Exhibition history: Exhibited: 1995 Feb-May, Atlanta, Emory University, Reflections of Women in the New Kingdom 2015-2016 4 Dec-27 Mar, Korea, Seoul Arts Centre, Human Image
